        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-23 17:46:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Hi Mandeep,\n > \n > currently CLI uses 30261 and i believe sdnc will have something\n > different. How it is conflicting with sdnc ? As CLI already uses\n > this port i would like to understand before committing the changes.\n > \n > Thanks.\n\nHi Kanagaraj, out of the box you are right there is no conflict, but SDNC has an optional S3P feature for geo-redundancy that when enabled, uses the same port 30261:\n./sdnc/values.yaml:  geoNodePort1: 61\n./cli/values.yaml:  nodePort1: 61",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
